          h2 Usage
          p
            | Cards display content composed of different elements whose size or supported
            | actions vary.
          h2 Behavior
          p
            | Cards have a constant width and variable height. The maximum height is limited to
            | the height of the available space on a platform, but it can temporarily expand (for
            | example, to display a comment field).
          p Cards do not flip over to reveal information on the back.
          h2 When to use
          p
            | Use a card layout when displaying content that:
            ul
              li As a collection, comprises multiple data types, such as images, movies, and text
              li
                | Does not require direct comparison (a user is not directly comparing images or text)
              li Supports content of highly variable length, such as comments
              li Contains interactive content, such as +1 buttons or comments
              li
                | Would otherwise be in a grid list but needs to display more content to supplement
                | the image
          h2 Supported gestures
          h3 Swipe
          p
            | The swipe gesture may be used on a per-card basis. Limit swipe gestures within a view so that they donâ€™t overlap with one another. For example, a swipeable card should not contain a swipeable image carousel, so that only a single action occurs when the card is swiped.
          h3 Pick-up-and-move
          p
            | The pick-up-and-move gesture may be used if it is important for the user to be able to sort cards within a collection. But consider if filtering or sorting would better organize the content.

